| **Topic**        | **Description**                                                                                                 |
| ---------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Full Form**    | Recurrent Neural Network (RNN)                                                                                  |
| **Definition**   | RNN is a deep learning algorithm designed to process **sequential data** such as text, speech, and time series. |
| **Main Feature** | It remembers information from previous inputs using a **hidden state (memory)**.                                |
| **Input**        | Sequence of words, numbers, or time-series values.                                                              |
| **Output**       | Prediction at each time step or at the end of the sequence.                                                     |
| **Memory**       | Stores previous information using a hidden state.                                                               |
| **Best For**     | Language Translation, Text Generation, Sentiment Analysis, Speech Recognition, Time Series Forecasting.         |
| **Limitation**   | Suffers from the **Vanishing Gradient Problem**, making it difficult to learn long-term dependencies.           |
| **Solution**     | LSTM and GRU were developed to overcome this limitation.                                                        |


==============

RNN Workflow
-----------

| **Step** | **Description**                                             |
| -------- | ----------------------------------------------------------- |
| 1        | Receive the first input word.                               |
| 2        | Store information in the hidden state.                      |
| 3        | Process the next word along with the previous hidden state. |
| 4        | Update the hidden state.                                    |
| 5        | Continue until all words are processed.                     |
| 6        | Produce the final output or prediction.                     |

==========

RNN vs LSTM vs GRU
------------------

| **Feature**            | **RNN**    | **LSTM**  | **GRU**          |
| ---------------------- | ---------- | --------- | ---------------- |
| Memory                 | Short-term | Long-term | Long-term        |
| Handles Long Sequences | ❌ No       | ✅ Yes     | ✅ Yes            |
| Vanishing Gradient     | ❌ Yes      | ✅ Solved  | ✅ Solved         |
| Speed                  | Fast       | Slower    | Faster than LSTM |
| Translation Accuracy   | Moderate   | High      | High             |


=========
RNN (Recurrent Neural Network) is a deep learning model designed for sequential data. 
It processes one element at a time and maintains a hidden state that stores information from previous inputs. 
This makes it suitable for applications such as language translation, sentiment analysis, speech recognition, 
and time-series forecasting. However, standard RNNs have difficulty learning long-term dependencies due to the vanishing gradient problem, 
which is why LSTM and GRU are commonly used instead.

